ol.li: Privilege Elevation: The finit_module syscall transitions the CPU context from Ring 3 to Ring 0 via int 0x80 or syscall instruction.
Relocation: The kernel loader performs the work a dynamic linker (ld.so) would usually do in userspace, resolving GOT/PLT entries within kernel space.
Symbol Table: External dependencies (e.g., printk) are resolved against the vmlinux global exported symbol table (EXPORT_SYMBOL).
Memory Management: The module's memory is initially RW-, then transitioned to R-X (Non-Writable and Executable) after initialization to satisfy security (W^X) requirements.
